            <p><strong><a href="http://arstechnica.com/tech-policy/2016/10/house-wants-briefing-as-soon-as-possible-to-grok-how-yahoo-spied/" target="_blank">House Wants “Briefing as soon as possible” to Grok How Yahoo Spied</a></strong></p>
            <p>Members of Congress have demanded answers from the Attorney General and Director of National Intelligence regarding reports that Yahoo received and complied with a 2015 government request to conduct warrantless searches of all users’ incoming email. Elected officials have expressed concerns over the constitutionality of such a request, and are calling for increased oversight of government intelligence programs.</p>
