            <p><strong><a href="https://techcrunch.com/2016/10/13/google-helps-speak-truth-to-power-adds-prominence-to-fact-checks-in-news/" target="_blank">Google Starts Highlighting Fact-Checks in News</a></strong></p>
            <p>Google recently announced that it has created a “fact-checker” tag for use in Google News. Content creators can add the tag themselves before posting stories, and the fact-check tag will be visible to users in the expanded view of new stories in both the desktop and mobile versions of Google News. The company indicated that the recent proliferation of fact-checking sites was one of its motivations in creating this service.</p>
