            <p><strong><a href="https://techcrunch.com/2016/10/04/twitter-microsoft-and-google-say-they-havent-scanned-messages-like-yahoo/" target="_blank">Twitter, Microsoft, Google and Others Say They Haven’t Scanned Messages Like Yahoo</a></strong></p>
            <p>Following recent reports that Yahoo built custom software to scan all incoming user email in response to a secret court order, other tech giants have swiftly distanced themselves from any notion that they participated in similar programs. Companies including Google and Twitter have stated that they have never received such a request from the government, and would oppose it if they did.</p>
